Interface NestedCollectionRoutes<T,S,U>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - the model's type

    U - the type of the parent model's identifier (e.g., Long, String, etc.)
    Deprecated. 
    As of 1.9.0, use Actions annotations instead

    @Deprecated
 @ProviderType
public interface NestedCollectionRoutes<T,S,U>
    Holds information about the routes supported for a NestedCollectionRouter.

    This interface's methods return functions to get the collection resource's different endpoints. You should always use a NestedCollectionRoutes.Builder to create instances of this interface.
